{"title":"Mallick Hossain","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Mallick Hossain","subtitle":"Senior Financial Economist","image":"images/avatar.jpg","about":{"template":"trestles","image-shape":"round","links":[{"icon":"linkedin","text":"","href":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mallickhossain/"},{"icon":"github","text":"","href":"https://github.com/emallickhossain"},{"icon":"google","text":"Scholar","href":"https://scholar.google.com.my/citations?hl=en&user=22Vq08IAAAAJ"},{"icon":"envelope","text":"","href":"mailto:your.email@philadelphiafed.org"},{"icon":"file-pdf","text":"CV","href":"files/HossainCV.pdf"}]}},"headingText":"Bio","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\nI am a senior financial economist at the Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia. My research interests are in consumer finance, health economics, and disaster risk and insurance. Previously, I worked as a Staff Economist for President Obama's Council of Economic Advisers and for the Census Bureau. \n\n*The views expressed here are my own and do not necessarily represent the views of the Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia or the Federal Reserve System.*\n\n## Recent Research\n\n- [Not Cashing In on Cashing Out: An Analysis of Low Cash-Out Refinance Rates (Accepted at *Real Estate Economics*)](http://doi.org/10.1111/1540-6229.70031) (with Igor Livshis and Collin Wardius)\n- [Pricing Protection: Credit Scores, Disaster Risk, and Home Insurance Affordability](https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=5026600) (with Joshua Blonz, Ben Keys, Philip Mulder, and Joakim Weill) was cited by the NYTimes in a recent [article](https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2026/03/09/climate/home-insurance-credit-scores.html)!\n\n[See all research →](research.qmd)\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n## Bio\n\nI am a senior financial economist at the Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia. My research interests are in consumer finance, health economics, and disaster risk and insurance. Previously, I worked as a Staff Economist for President Obama's Council of Economic Advisers and for the Census Bureau. \n\n*The views expressed here are my own and do not necessarily represent the views of the Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia or the Federal Reserve System.*\n\n## Recent Research\n\n- [Not Cashing In on Cashing Out: An Analysis of Low Cash-Out Refinance Rates (Accepted at *Real Estate Economics*)](http://doi.org/10.1111/1540-6229.70031) (with Igor Livshis and Collin Wardius)\n- [Pricing Protection: Credit Scores, Disaster Risk, and Home Insurance Affordability](https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=5026600) (with Joshua Blonz, Ben Keys, Philip Mulder, and Joakim Weill) was cited by the NYTimes in a recent [article](https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2026/03/09/climate/home-insurance-credit-scores.html)!\n\n[See all research →](research.qmd)\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon"